# Brand Guidelines

When editing UI, styles, or content, follow the brand. Full reference: `data/brand-guidelines.md`, `data/canva-brand-colors.md`.

## Colors

| Role          | Hex                  | Use                                   |
| ------------- | -------------------- | ------------------------------------- |
| Primary       | `#6b8e23`            | Links, buttons, CTAs, key UI, borders |
| Primary light | `#e8f5d0`, `#c8e7c0` | Hover, light backgrounds              |
| Secondary     | `#a8f7b5`            | Accents, secondary buttons            |
| Gray text     | `#3a3229`            | Body text                             |
| Gray bg       | `#fef8f2`            | Light backgrounds                     |

**Do:** One main primary action per screen; gray for text and calm backgrounds.  
**Don’t:** Primary for long body text; no new accent colors beyond primary/secondary/gray.

Full swatches (50–950): `data/canva-brand-colors.md`.

## Voice (copy / Hebrew content)

- **Tone:** Casual, approachable; first person (אני, שלי). Playful when it fits.
- **Focus:** DevX, open source, practical tech.
- **Language:** Hebrew (he-IL), RTL where relevant.
- **Avoid:** Formal, unexplained jargon, salesy tone.

## Assets

- **Profile / “me”:** `baruch.png` — light or warm neutral backgrounds.
- **Logo mark:** `logo.png` — headers, social.
- **Social / cover:** `site-cover.png`.

Don’t stretch, recolor, or place on busy backgrounds.

## Typography

- **Sans:** Space Grotesk (variable) — headings and UI. Headings bold and tight; body readable.
